Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Elastic Mie Scattering and Effective Contrast Extraction", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"57db7344-7e45-4c8a-9b73-e8c5d1f60e0f"],

Cell["T. M. Nestor \[Dash] Research School of Earth Sciences, ANU", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"0c9065ec-8dfb-4d5a-8789-4b1a244497ea"],

Cell["\<\
Computes the exact elastic Mie scattering coefficients for a sphere and \
extracts effective contrasts via Legendre projection. Validates against the \
Eshelby-corrected Rayleigh T-matrix, demonstrating exact agreement at all \
contrast levels in the ka \[Rule] 0 limit.

References:
  Pao & Mow (1973) \[Dash] Diffraction of Elastic Waves
  Korneev & Johnson (1993) \[Dash] Scattering of elastic waves by a sphere
  Shekhar et al. (2023) \[Dash] Lippmann\[Dash]Schwinger T-matrix
  Eshelby (1957) \[Dash] Elastic field of an ellipsoidal inclusion\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"951098d8-e4a1-4731-9751-46021a034a16"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["1. Spherical Bessel/Hankel Functions", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ab07321e-28af-4b7c-b050-fa5c162c8a9a"],

Cell["\<\
Mathematica has built-in SphericalBesselJ, SphericalBesselY, \
SphericalHankelH1.  We define wrappers and derivatives via the recurrence \
relation:
  j_n\[CloseCurlyQuote](z) = (n/z) j_n(z) \[Minus] j_{n+1}(z)
  h_n\[CloseCurlyQuote](z) = (n/z) h_n(z) \[Minus] h_{n+1}(z)\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a6923e0c-cc1d-49f7-90f9-ae0ef0da8152"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
(* Spherical Bessel/Hankel functions *)
jn[n_, z_] := SphericalBesselJ[n, z];
yn[n_, z_] := SphericalBesselY[n, z];
hn[n_, z_] := SphericalHankelH1[n, z];

(* Derivatives via recurrence relation *)
jnp[n_, z_] := (n/z) jn[n, z] - jn[n + 1, z];
hnp[n_, z_] := (n/z) hn[n, z] - hn[n + 1, z];

(* Verification *)
Print[\"Check j_0(z) = Sin[z]/z: \",
  FullSimplify[jn[0, z] - Sin[z]/z] === 0];
Print[\"Check h_0(z) = -i exp(iz)/z: \",
  FullSimplify[hn[0, z] - (-I Exp[I z]/z)] === 0];\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:=",ExpressionUUID->"d872dbc9-92cd-424f-9434-e6561b82803d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 InterpretationBox[
  RowBox[{"\<\"Check j_0(z) = Sin[z]/z: \"\>", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "True"}],
  SequenceForm["Check j_0(z) = Sin[z]/z: ", True],
  Editable->False]], "Print",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.981944965577642*^9},
 CellLabel->
