Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["9. Eshelby Delta Function Derivation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"246db64a-9a10-4d6e-ad61-3183a3fd4146"],

Cell["\<\
The Green\[CloseCurlyQuote]s tensor second derivative integral I_{ijkl} = \
\[Integral]_V G_{ij,kl} d\\[ThreeSuperior]x has a distributional \
\[Delta]-function from the 1/r singularity.

In the static limit (\[Omega] \[Rule] 0):
  f(r) \[Rule] F/r  where F = (\[Lambda]+3\[Mu]) / (8\[Pi]\[Mu](\[Lambda]+2\
\[Mu]))
  g(r) \[Rule] G/r  where G = (\[Lambda]+\[Mu]) / (8\[Pi]\[Mu](\[Lambda]+2\
\[Mu]))

For h(r) = 3F/r + G/r = H/r:
  h\[CloseCurlyQuote] = \[Minus]H/r\\[TwoSuperior],  h\[CloseCurlyQuote]\
\[CloseCurlyQuote] = 2H/r\\[ThreeSuperior]

The \[CapitalGamma]_1 integrand = (4\[Pi]/3)(2H/r\\[ThreeSuperior]) + \
(8\[Pi]/3)(\[Minus]H/r\\[TwoSuperior])/r = 0

Similarly q = f\[CloseCurlyQuote] + g\[CloseCurlyQuote] + 2g/r = \
(G\[Minus]F)/r\\[TwoSuperior] in the static limit,
so the \[CapitalGamma]_2 integrand also vanishes identically.

Both integrands vanish in the static limit \[DoubleRightArrow] ALL of A, B \
comes from the distributional \[Delta]-function that numerical quadrature \
completely misses.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e90de4c5-93ce-4c58-8003-2fceef968307"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
(* Symbolic verification: static integrands vanish *)
Fsym = (lam + 3 mu)/(8 Pi mu (lam + 2 mu));
Gsym = (lam + mu)/(8 Pi mu (lam + 2 mu));
Hsym = 3 Fsym + Gsym;

Print[\"Static Green's tensor coefficients:\"];
Print[\"  F = \", Fsym];
Print[\"  G = \", Gsym];
Print[\"  H = 3F + G = \", Simplify[Hsym]];

(* \[CapitalGamma]_1 integrand: r^2 [(4\[Pi]/3) h'' + (8\[Pi]/3) h'/r] *)
(* For h = H/r: h' = -H/r^2, h'' = 2H/r^3 *)
g1static = r^2 ((4 Pi/3)(2 Hsym/r^3) + (8 Pi/3)(-Hsym/r^2)/r);
Print[\"\\n\[CapitalGamma]_1 integrand (static) = \", Simplify[g1static], \"  \
(= 0!)\"];

(* q = f' + g' + 2g/r for static case *)
qstatic = (Gsym - Fsym)/r^2;
qpstatic = -2 (Gsym - Fsym)/r^3;
g2static = r^2 ((4 Pi/3) qpstatic + (8 Pi/3) qstatic/r);
Print[\"\[CapitalGamma]_2 integrand (static) = \", Simplify[g2static], \"  (= \
0!)\"];

Print[\"\\nBoth integrands vanish \[DoubleRightArrow] ALL of A, B is from the \
\[Delta]-function.\"];\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[152]:=",ExpressionUUID->"0b604844-abf0-4657-8207-0a6fafdf9fb9"],

